
"Where does ChatGPT fit in the AI hierarchy?"

A strong answer is:

"ChatGPT is a Generative AI application powered by a Large Language Model (LLM). 
The LLM is built using Deep Learning, which is a subset of Machine Learning, 
and Machine Learning itself is a subset of Artificial Intelligence.
ChatGPT mainly works on Natural Language Processing tasks such as understanding and generating human language."


| Traditional NLP        | GenAI                                   |
| ---------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| Remove stop words      | Usually not required                    |
| Stemming               | Usually not required                    |
| Lemmatization          | Usually not required                    |
| TF-IDF                 | Usually not required for the LLM itself |
| Chunking               | ✅ Required for RAG                      |
| HTML cleaning          | ✅ Common                                |
| OCR cleaning           | ✅ Common                                |
| PII masking            | ✅ Common                                |
| Prompt formatting      | ✅ Very common                           |
| Document summarization | ✅ Common                                |

